==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mineralogy
<hw>Min`er*al"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Mineralogies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[<ets>Mineral</ets> +
<ets>-logy</ets>: cf. F. <ets>min⟦eacute⟧ralogie</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The science which treats of minerals, and teaches
how to describe, distinguish, and classify them.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A treatise or book on this science.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- minerology, minerological = misspelling for mineralogy,
mineralogical -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Minerva</ent>⟦br⟧
